    <h2 class="title"><a href="/2010/10/06/broken-meetings">Video: &quot;Broken Meetings (and how you&#039;ll fix them)&quot;</a></h2>
  		<span class="submitted">
  		<a href="/people/merlin-mann">Merlin Mann</a>  |  Oct 6 2010	</span>

  <div class="content"><!-- google_ad_section_start --><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/15579561?color=ffffff" width="521" height="345" frameborder="0"></iframe>

<!-- 
* Direct Video DL (mov)
* Direct Audio DL (mp3)
-->

<p>A couple weeks ago, my pals at <a href="http://Twitter.com">Twitter</a>  were kind enough to invite me in to visit with their (rapidly growing) team. The topic was <em>meetings</em>, so I used it as an opportunity to publicly premiere a talk I&#8217;ve been presenting to private clients over the past few&nbsp;months.</p>

<p>I hope you&#8217;ll enjoy, <a href="http://vimeo.com/15579561"><strong>Broken Meetings (and how you&#8217;ll &#xfb01;x them)</strong></a>.</p>

<p><a href="http://i-0.us/meetings-deck"><strong>Slides</strong></a>:</p>

